Easiest Ever Biscuits
  --Cook's Illustrated

3 c (15 oz) ap flour
4 tsp sugar
1 tbsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1 1/4 tsp salt
2 c heavy cream
2 tbsp unsalted butter, melted (optional)

Adjust oven rack to upper middle position and heat to 450F. Line rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. In medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Microwave cream until just warmed to body temp (95-100F), 60-90 s, stirring halfway through. Stir cream into flour mixture until soft, uniform dough forms. Spray 1/2 c dry measure cup with vegetable oil spray. Drop level scoops of batter 2" apart on prepared sheet; biscuitsshould be ~2 1/2" wide and 1 1/4" tall. Respray cup every 3-4 scoops. Bake until tops are light golden brown, 10-12 min, rotating sheet halfway through baking. Brush hot biscuits with melted butter, if using. Serve warm. Biscuits can be stored in airtight bag at room temp for up to 24hrs.

